# AI Working State
Last updated: 2026-07-07 (latency round 2: SQLite synchronous=NORMAL)

This file holds ONLY globally-useful state: the single thing most recently/
currently worked on (with a pointer to its full state), an index of the per-spec
state files, the release log, and the cross-cutting decisions/preferences.

**Detailed, spec-scoped working state lives in `state/<track>.md`** — one file
per spec, each linked from its spec's header. Read AI.state first; then read only
the `state/` file for the track you're touching. See CLAUDE.md "AI working state"
for the protocol (how to keep this single-latest and where new notes go).

## Latest
Latency round 3: after v3.0.1 (batch-window opt-out + synchronous=NORMAL,
see `state/bundled-examples.md`) a quick on→off still lags ~500 ms —
diagnosed as the synchronous ha.call_service parking the script event
loop until HA's result frame (sent only after the service completes,
Zigbee round trip included). Wrote `event-latency-spec.md`: opt-in
`{ wait = false }` for call_service + memory-authoritative state mirror
with a background batched SQLite writer. **Awaiting user review before
build.** Details in `state/event-latency.md`.

