## Key decisions (do not re-litigate without good reason)
- **State scope**: full history log (append-only) + current-state mirror for fast get_state
- **Lua concurrency**: one LState per script goroutine, never shared
- **Script registration**: in-script (ha.on_state_change style), no external manifest
- **KV encoding**: JSON round-trip via github.com/go-json-experiment/json (json/v2)
- **Global KV**: separate global_kv table (not a reserved script_id in script_kv); no proxy — use global.get/set directly
- **Timer IDs (every/at)**: stable key = script_id|type|spec|N; INSERT OR IGNORE preserves last_run/next_run across reloads
- **Timer IDs (after)**: UUID per call; row deleted after firing; orphaned rows cleaned up on startup
- **ha.after persistence**: best-effort — survives restart only if called at load time; callback-registered timers are dropped and logged on restart
- **Catch-up semantics**: fire at most once per missed timer (not replay all missed intervals)
- **Scheduler coupling**: scheduler sends TimerFiredEvent via onFire callback → script channel; scheduler does not hold *lua.LFunction references
- **HA add-on**: repo root = add-on directory; supervisor injects SUPERVISOR_TOKEN + ws://supervisor/core/websocket; scripts at /config/ha-lua/scripts/ (HA config dir mounted at /config via homeassistant_config + path:/config, like ESPHome — NOT addon_config, which hides files in a private /addon_configs/<slug> folder); DB at /data/ha-lua.db; user options from /data/options.json
- **Core REST API**: ha.set_state/remove_state ride POST/DELETE /api/states/{id}; the REST base is DERIVED from the WS URL in ha.New (no config field); bindings are NON-RAISING (value|nil,err) so per-minute publishers can't spam on_exception
- **Card assets**: bundled in the `cards/` embed package and Materialized to /config/www/ha-lua on boot (served at /local/ha-lua/...); a card fix only reaches a user after a new image + add-on restart. The card needs an admin HA user to fire ha_lua_command
- **Config**: production reads /data/options.json; development uses --config flag pointing to config.dev.yaml
- **Logging**: slog TextHandler writes to stderr (Supervisor add-on log) and, when cfg.LogDir set, also to <LogDir>/ha-lua.log via io.MultiWriter; add-on mode forces LogDir=/config/ha-lua/logs, dev leaves it empty (stderr only). File open is best-effort (warn + stderr-only on failure). NO rotation yet. ha.exceptions.log_file MkdirAll's the parent
- **Lua sandbox**: SkipOpenLibs=true; open base/math/string/table/os/coroutine selectively; nil out load/loadfile/dofile/io/debug/package/os.execute/os.exit; replace require with restricted loader (scripts/lib/ only)
- **Error handling**: every callback dispatch wrapped in pcall; on error build exception info table {script_id, error, traceback, callback, event, timestamp} and call registered on_exception handler; slog.Error fallback if no handler; ha.exceptions.email uses net/smtp, ha.exceptions.log_file uses os.OpenFile append
- **JSON library**: github.com/go-json-experiment/json everywhere — strict UTF-8; import path changes to encoding/json/v2 when stdlib proposal lands. Deterministic key order is NOT the default: every marshal site that needs stable output must pass json.Deterministic(true) (luaMarshal does)
- **Lua stdlib modules**: strings, time, json (v2), re (kept — user explicitly disagreed with cutting it), http, crypto (md5/sha1/sha256/sha512/hmac_sha256/hmac_sha512/base64/hex/rand/equal); math augmentation (round/clamp/log2/sign)
- **call_service**: SYNCHRONOUS since 2.3.0 — SendCommandWaitResult registers a waiter by msg id, routes the "result" frame back, success:false -> error carrying HA's message; 10s timeout + drain-on-disconnect. FireEvent stays fire-and-forget
- **Tests**: real SQLite (:memory:) everywhere, no mocks; table-driven; helpers in internal/testutil/db.go. Browser tests via chromedp, skip cleanly with no browser. Card: node --check + chromedp harness against the embed FS
- **Benchmark regression**: benchstat comparison is informational only — bench-compare target prints output but does not fail the build; no cmd/bench-check tool
- **Purge**: single DELETE for rows older than retention_days (default 2); no downsampling; no stats tables; Purger.RunOnce() for tests
- **Retention config**: state_history.retention_days default 2; purge_interval default "1h"
- **Purge cutoff**: computed in Go as RFC3339 and bound as a parameter — never datetime('now',...) in SQL (format mismatch vs RFC3339 changed_at breaks string comparison)
- **Seed dedup**: state_history row on seed only when state/attributes differ from mirror (reconnects must not pollute history)
- **require semantics**: per-LState loaded-module cache + circular-require error (not bare DoFile)
- **http timeout**: shared client with a fixed 30s Timeout (stdlib_http.go) + the script's lifetime context; no per-callback context and no timeout config option (the old "callback context (5s)" note was never implemented)
- **Email cooldown**: per-script window (config.cooldown, default "15m"), suppressed errors counted and reported in next send; log_file is unlimited (but size-capped: active + one .1 backup)
- **Rooted filesystem IO (v3.0.0)**: TWO process-wide os.Roots — scripts root (fs module incl. write/append/mkdir/remove, require, LoadAll enumeration) and logs root over log_dir (ha.exceptions.log_file, relative paths only, raises at registration on abs/../unset log_dir)
- **ha.at timezone**: timezone config option → $TZ → UTC-with-warning; time/tzdata embedded; next_run stored UTC. main also sets time.Local from the timezone so script time.now() agrees with the scheduler
- **Prod config channel**: /data/options.json + $SUPERVISOR_TOKEN only; run.sh passes no flags
- **golangci-lint**: v2.12.2 (config format version "2"); a `tool` dependency in go.mod alongside staticcheck and benchstat — run via `go tool golangci-lint run`, never go install or a release binary; errcheck excludes deferred-cleanup calls (Tx.Rollback, Rows.Close, DB.Close, websocket Conn.CloseNow, fsnotify Watcher.Close, os.Root.Close) — configure the tool, don't litter the code with `_ =`
- **Tool dependencies**: staticcheck, benchstat, golangci-lint are `tool` directives in go.mod (Go 1.24+ idiom; tools.go removed). `make` targets call them as `go tool <name>`. Root `make install-tools` only runs `go mod download`; nothing lands in a bin dir
- **SQLite DSN**: modernc.org/sqlite pragmas use `_pragma=name(value)` — mattn-style params are silently ignored; any new DB open site must use the modernc form (TestOpenDBEnablesWAL is the canary)
- **SQLite synchronous=NORMAL** (not the FULL default): every state_changed commits on the write handle before dispatch, and at FULL that fsync's jitter (ms–tens of ms on HA flash) lands directly on script handler latency. WAL+NORMAL loses at most the last commits on power cut, never corrupts; the mirror re-seeds from HA, history is throwaway, timers rebuild at load — do NOT "fix durability" back to FULL
- **Script stop semantics**: drain (close channel) not kill; 5s grace then per-script context cancel aborts the VM; registry removal always precedes channel close
- **Hot reload trigger**: debounce 300ms per script, then stat the file — present → reload, absent → stop; never decide from fsnotify event types (atomic saves lie). The watcher only watches .lua — editing a sibling .html alone does NOT reload
- **Seed delivery**: client.States stays open forever, capacity 1, newest batch wins; one batch per (re)connect
- **Event batching**: 100 ms per-script coalescing window (runner.go batchWindow) is the default because unbatched bursts REALLY dropped events (overflowed script channels) before batching existed; latency-sensitive scripts opt out per-script via ha.immediate_events() (do NOT make immediate the default or lower the window). Tracker write stays BEFORE Dispatch in main.go — handlers read fresh state via ha.get_state
- **Lua VM stays gopher-lua**: arnodel/golua (Lua 5.4/5.5) evaluated 2026-06-13 and rejected — v0.x single-maintainer vs battle-tested v1.x; CPS binding API is more verbose than LState stack API across ~30 bindings; M6 stop semantics depend on SetContext; 5.3+ integers would split the number type through the whole JSON layer. Reasons documented in README. Revisit only if golua hits 1.0 AND Lua 5.1 becomes a real script-author problem
- **Card components**: the Lovelace card uses plain HTML + HA CSS theme variables, NOT HA's undocumented styling primitives (ha-button/ha-switch/...), which churn across releases. It DOES use the load-safe ones: <ha-card>, <ha-icon>, and ha-entity-picker/ha-entities-picker in the config editor (flagged as version-fragile). No build step, no imports — one vanilla file
- **No vendoring**: vendor/ measures 241MB (226MB = modernc.org); go.sum + module proxy pin and preserve everything; `go mod vendor` is one command away if hermetic offline builds are ever needed
- **Dependency updates**: `make update-deps` (go get -u -t ./... + go get -u tool + tidy); analyzers update via the tool meta-pattern

## Removed (do not add back without explicit user request)
- state_stats_hourly / state_stats_daily tables
- ha.get_stats
- is_numeric column on state_history
- 4-step transactional purge (aggregate → hourly → daily → delete)
- global.state() persistent-proxy (cache coherency issue with concurrent scripts)
- cmd/bench-check tool (over-engineered for a home project)

## User preferences observed
- Studio Code Server is the editor; scripts live at /config/ha-lua/scripts/
- Pure Go only — modernc.org/sqlite (no CGO), gopher-lua (no CGO)
- Deployment target: HA add-on (single static binary + /data + HA config dir mounted at /config)
- Prefers planning to be done before any code is written
- Wants code written in the persona of Linus Torvalds; avoid needless complexity
